article.headline: Stony Brook 72, Hartford 63
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. -- Bryan Dougher and Demetrius Young scored 21 points apiece and Stony Brook led all the way in a 72-63 victory over Hartford on Sunday. Tom Brenton added 17 points and 14 rebounds for the Seawolves (11-9, 3-4 America East), who held a 29-18 lead at the half. Jaret Von Rosenberg scored 21 points to lead the Hawks (6-15, 2-5), Genesis Maciel added 13, and Michael Turner had nine points and 10 rebounds. Dougher and El Amin Muhammad each had 3-pointers in the Seawolves' opening 16-3 run. They increased their advantage to 45-28 on a Young's jumper at 13:30. Von Rosenberg hit a 3 to get Hartford within 48-44 with 9:56 to play.
